<p align="justify">On the autumnal equinox, the sun shines directly on the equator and the day and night are divided equally, while the heat gradually fades and the weather turns cool. To welcome the autumnal equinox, schools and kindergartens in China carried out various activities to help the students to learn about the knowledge of traditional solar terms and feel the traditional folk culture.</p>
